    • onActionDeleteProduct

      void onActionDeleteProduct(javafx.event.ActionEvent event)
      This method is called when the user clicks the Delete button in the Products section. It deletes the selected product from the inventory if a product is selected. It displays an error message if no product is selected or if the product has associated parts.

      private void setProductsTableView()
      This method sets the products tableview to display all products in the inventory.

    • setProductSearchListener

      private void setProductSearchListener()
      This method sets up the listeners for the products search bar. It selects a specific product with the given ID if the search bar contains only numbers. Otherwise, it filters the products table by the search bar text. If the search bar is empty, it displays all products. If the search bar text doesn't match any product, it displays an error message.
